tip.text: Super, super awesome lunch! Presentation of food was beatiful, very attentive service, everything in the menu looked very interesting! Loved pork buns, pumpkin salad, special seafood rice...
The lounge music here is out of this world. The terrace makes you feel like you're in another space.

formattedAddress: 5th Floor, 240 Regent St (Entrance on 30 Argyll St)

tip.text: Super super cute dessert!! Great for Instagram. It's delicious too! I had the matcha soft cream with egg waffle. So nice!

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia West Mall, Lt. 3A (Jl. M.H. Thamrin No. 1)

tip.text: Very nice interiors, good for date, food was great. What else do you ask for? Coming from Singapore, I don't think the food is expensive. Spaghetti with crab and cherry tomato sauce was delish.

formattedAddress: Menara Bank Danamon, Ground Floor (Lingkar Mega Kuningan)

tip.text: Great staff service! They don't speak English well, they're very nice. Breakfast was satisfactory (fruits, Nasi Goreng, egg station, dessert, Indo rice cakes). Nasi Goreng Fave-I-rite was great!
Great bagel sandwiches! I tried the Sriracha one with Cajun spiced chicken, and the Piglet breakfast bagel sandwich. Both were very good!
Cheap banh mis. Noodles are good but a little salty.
Burrata was good, with pomegranate on top. Salmon dish is new but very flavorful with the green pea sauce. Turkish bread and pita bread are both good.

formattedAddress: 15 Stamford Rd, #01-84, Capitol Singapore (15 Stamford Road)

tip.text: Had the best seller soy and lemongrass chicken. Not good value for money.
Service is super slow. Food was decent. Peacocks walk around you as you eat. Semi-Infinity pool at your sight.

Nice brunch spot. Wait outside to queue. Seats are not the most comfortable but the organic eggs Benedict was great. Kale juice is pricey for the size. Dessert we had sweet potato carrot cake, not bad
Super awesome authentic Chinese Szechuan food! It's our tradition to come here after a major event. The spiciness is right on point!! Love it and highly recommend this place!!
Lovely wedding venue.
Raisin scones and campaign before brunch were nice! Crab meat/salmon Benedicts were just okay. Lovely place for brunch though!
Awesome food! The falafel and salad were good! You can add meat, gyro and whatever to it.
Lobster wontons was my fav TAO dish. Angry dragon roll was average. Chilean sea bass (entree) was very good. Overall good quality is one level down to Hakkasan, but the interiors were very cool.

formattedAddress: 3377 Las Vegas Blvd S (in The Venetian)

tip.text: Modern and clean atmosphere, sunny, creative and floral. Red quinoa salad and the quiche (off menu) were good. Pizza, potato salad were okay.
Two levels of wine tasting, both are good. Always fun to walk around, enjoy the view, see the pool, teepee and bocce ball court. Great wine bottle designs! Many cool things to shop.

Paella is great. Bacon wrapped dates is a good choice in every restaurant. Creamy chicken croquettes were a bit salty. Duck meatball slider & crab toast were good but not amazing. Nice vibe and music.
Not as amazing as everyone says. Bahn mi roti has great Panang sauce, shaking beef has nice flavors, popcorn shrimp was just ok, seabass was true to the fish's original flavor. Empress rice was nice.

The baneffee pie was too sweet, the banana ice cream sandwich was better. They serve nice pretzel bread. The lobster bisque and Mexican drunken shrimp were okay.

Very nice vibe, great wines at reasonable prices. A large pitcher of sangria was only $20. Food and service were great. I love the pork belly tostada and soy ginger salmon. They also have low-cal menu
Loved it! The bison burger was great, the refreshing juice (Bright Eyes) was very good. Edamame dumplings were comforting. Chia seed dessert was delicious. Look forward to its Chicago location!
Rooftop is nice. Happy Hour for tenants everyday, frequent international mixers and other events are happening.
It's a fun place! Endeavor is here! You can touch star fish and other kinds of water creatures. Free admission
Good for groups, authentic taste, nice service. Parking is relatively easy too.
Love the brunch menu! Chicken waffle is a must. All the crispy rice patty dishes are good. Sweet potato caterpillars sushi is good. Mimosas are good but small! You can pay with opentable.

tip.text: Third time having dinner here. Consistent high quality and nice decor. Cauliflower salad, cod ravioli and duck breast were great. Date with divinity was a good light cocktail.
